name: Direct power coupling
description: Direct power coupling has a central power capacitor that feeds power directly to each system.

name: Directional shield
description: Directional Shields are the most commonly used and balanced shields on the market.

name: Discord missile
description: On a failed saving throw, the missile deploys pistoeka sabotage or �buzz� droids on the target. At the end of each of the target ship�s turns, the target ship gains one level of system damage if the target is medium or smaller [large or smaller]. As an action on each of their turns, a crewmember can have the ship attempt their choice of a dexterity or constitution saving throw (DC 15), ending the effect on a success.

name: Distributed power coupling
description: Distributed power coupling sacrifices flexibility by allocating power separately to each system.

name: Flechette torpedo
description: A Flechette torpedo detonates at a point within range, creating a 200 (400) foot cube of difficult terrain.  Any ship entering or starting their turn in this area must succeed at a Dexterity saving throw (DC 15) or take 1d8 [2d8] kinetic damage.

name: Fortress shield
description: Fortress shields offer a higher maximum shield points, but regenerate slower than normal shields.

name: Fuel cell reactor
description: Fuel cell reactors are the most common and balanced reactors on the market.

name: Hub & spoke power coupling
description: A hub and spoke coupling system combines attributes of both other systems, providing some flexibility and some increased power storage capacity.

name: Ionization reactor
description: Ionization reactors are highly fuel-efficient reactors that trade power output for fuel economy.

name: Power core reactor
description: Power core reactors have highly variable power output capabilities, but sacrifice fuel economy and as a result.

name: Quick-Charge shield
description: Quick-Charge Shields, opposite of Fortress Shields, offer a reduced capacity, but rapidly replenish.

name: S-thread tracer
description: On a failed saving throw, the missile latches an S-thread tracer onto the target. When making an Intelligence (Probe) check to detect the S-threaded ship's hyperspace travel, its angle of departure can be detected on a roll of 15 instead of 25.

name: Sparkler ion cannon
properties: Power (range 200/800), auto, burst 1, ionizing, overheat 1, saturate

name: Twin auto-blaster
properties: Power (range 250/1000), auto, burst 10, hidden, overheat 20, rapid 5
